WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:04.000 line:0
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:01:50.300 --> 00:01:57.100
Dial Battle

3
00:01:57.100 --> 00:01:59.310
Hey! Where are you going, Zoro?!

4
00:01:59.310 --> 00:02:01.850
That's the wrong way!
West is over here!

5
00:02:01.850 --> 00:02:05.360
Man, your terrible sense
of direction is so annoying...

6
00:02:05.360 --> 00:02:06.610
West?

7
00:02:06.610 --> 00:02:08.320
But that's east!

8
00:02:08.320 --> 00:02:12.740
C'mon, Luffy! Why don't you
ever listen to anyone?!

9
00:02:12.740 --> 00:02:16.200
It's the "skull's right eye,"
so we gotta go right! Are you stupid?!

10
00:02:17.200 --> 00:02:22.000
We need to head south, so could 
you tell them to come this way?

11
00:02:22.000 --> 00:02:23.670
You got it!

12
00:02:27.420 --> 00:02:29.630
Luffy! Zoro!

13
00:02:31.670 --> 00:02:33.550
South, huh?

14
00:02:33.550 --> 00:02:35.680
Why didn't you say so sooner?

15
00:02:46.350 --> 00:02:48.900
♪ This stick is so sturdy! ♪

16
00:02:47.060 --> 00:02:50.940
That's a really nice stick, Luffy!

17
00:02:52.570 --> 00:02:56.070
Right? But you can't have it!
Go find your own!

18
00:02:57.200 --> 00:02:58.830
Lucky!

19
00:02:59.280 --> 00:03:00.830
A stick, a stick...!

20
00:03:01.200 --> 00:03:02.660
What about sticks?

21
00:03:03.870 --> 00:03:11.840
I thought this forest would be
a scarier place, but it's not so bad!

22
00:03:14.630 --> 00:03:18.010
Are you feeling confident
today, Chopper?

23
00:03:18.010 --> 00:03:19.640
That's right!

24
00:03:21.260 --> 00:03:23.980
I feel so safe with these three around!

25
00:03:24.390 --> 00:03:28.730
Honestly, this place
has been a huge letdown.

26
00:03:28.730 --> 00:03:33.230
There was nothing in
the forest yesterday, either.

27
00:03:33.230 --> 00:03:35.860
We didn't run across a single priest.

28
00:03:35.860 --> 00:03:38.200
I know how you feel, Chopper.

29
00:03:38.200 --> 00:03:39.450
Right?!

30
00:03:41.660 --> 00:03:43.750
What odd people.

31
00:03:43.750 --> 00:03:46.160
Are you that eager
for something bad to happen?

32
00:03:54.210 --> 00:03:55.550
Huh?

33
00:04:06.350 --> 00:04:07.560
Wh-What the...?!

34
00:04:06.680 --> 00:04:07.560
What?!

35
00:04:21.450 --> 00:04:24.450
The wind's good! The helm's good!

36
00:04:25.200 --> 00:04:27.870
How relaxing! What a perfect cruise!

37
00:04:28.370 --> 00:04:31.630
But this thing sure is slow!
Hey, navigator! Do something!

38
00:04:31.630 --> 00:04:33.880
I'm afraid I can't, Captain Usopp!

39
00:04:33.880 --> 00:04:38.220
The milky roads have intense bends,
so we have to rely on the Crow's dials!

40
00:04:38.220 --> 00:04:39.760
You can do it, Little Crow!

41
00:04:39.760 --> 00:04:41.300
Oh, and Sanji!

42
00:04:41.300 --> 00:04:44.140
Be at my guard at all times!

43
00:04:44.140 --> 00:04:46.720
Your captain is afraid of this forest...

44
00:04:46.720 --> 00:04:48.180
Shut up!

45
00:04:48.180 --> 00:04:51.060
The only one I'm protecting is Nami!

46
00:04:51.060 --> 00:04:54.440
Oh, yeah! It's time for
the weird knight's medicine!

47
00:04:54.440 --> 00:04:56.530
Where did Chopper say
he put it again?

48
00:04:56.530 --> 00:05:00.740
Gan Fall. My name is Gan Fall.

49
00:05:00.740 --> 00:05:01.660
Um...

50
00:05:01.660 --> 00:05:04.410
It's on a barrel next to the fridge.

51
00:05:04.410 --> 00:05:05.160
Thanks.

52
00:05:07.330 --> 00:05:08.540
Old man?

53
00:05:08.540 --> 00:05:12.330
Would you like to hear
a little of this land's history?

54
00:05:12.960 --> 00:05:13.790
Sure.

55
00:05:17.840 --> 00:05:19.720
So you've shown up again.

56
00:05:22.680 --> 00:05:24.010
Get out of here, old man!

57
00:05:25.890 --> 00:05:27.770
Stop, Wyper!

58
00:05:27.770 --> 00:05:30.140
Gan Fall has come to negotiate!

59
00:05:30.140 --> 00:05:31.350
Negotiate, my ass!

60
00:05:31.730 --> 00:05:33.650
Out of the way, Chief!

61
00:05:33.650 --> 00:05:39.650
Do you expect us to agree to
a compromise between two old men?!

62
00:05:39.650 --> 00:05:42.150
Listen, Gan Fall!

63
00:05:42.150 --> 00:05:44.320
We're not budging a single inch!

64
00:05:45.030 --> 00:05:48.410
If you insist that fighting
is pointless, then give it all back!

65
00:05:48.410 --> 00:05:53.420
Did you forget how your people have
treated Shandians for generations?!

66
00:05:54.040 --> 00:05:56.540
What's with wanting
coexistence now?!

67
00:05:57.040 --> 00:05:59.960
I cannot return everything.

68
00:05:59.960 --> 00:06:06.800
The power of Upper Yard's vearth
is essential to Skypiea now.

69
00:06:06.800 --> 00:06:10.220
The citizens are grateful
for its blessings.

70
00:06:10.680 --> 00:06:16.810
I could not possibly take
that away from innocent people!

71
00:06:16.810 --> 00:06:19.940
You say the sky people are innocent?

72
00:06:20.570 --> 00:06:24.660
That's only because they live
in peace and never have to fight!

73
00:06:24.660 --> 00:06:28.410
Should we bring people outside of
your Holy Host into our fight, then?!

74
00:06:28.410 --> 00:06:30.080
That's insane!

75
00:06:30.080 --> 00:06:32.750
You want forgiveness
for your sins? Prove it!

76
00:06:33.000 --> 00:06:37.080
Sacrifice 100 people who don't
wanna die and bring us their heads!

77
00:06:37.710 --> 00:06:39.920
I cannot do that!

78
00:06:41.840 --> 00:06:45.550
Then negotiations are over! Leave!

79
00:06:46.010 --> 00:06:49.100
Or I'll rip your head off
right here and now!

80
00:06:49.760 --> 00:06:51.850
Wait, Wyper!

81
00:06:54.520 --> 00:06:57.310
Don't use my name so freely.

82
00:06:58.940 --> 00:07:00.650
My...

83
00:07:01.110 --> 00:07:03.360
favorite drink...

84
00:07:03.360 --> 00:07:04.950
is pumpkin juice.

85
00:07:06.660 --> 00:07:08.200
I'll kill you!

86
00:07:08.700 --> 00:07:10.410
Wait, Wyper!

87
00:07:10.410 --> 00:07:13.120
Men! Stop Wyper!

88
00:07:13.120 --> 00:07:15.960
What are you doing,
Kamakiri and Braham?!

89
00:07:15.960 --> 00:07:17.540
Not you, too?!

90
00:07:25.720 --> 00:07:27.470
Auntie...

91
00:07:27.470 --> 00:07:29.720
Aisa certainly cries a lot, doesn't she?

92
00:07:30.470 --> 00:07:31.560
Yes.

93
00:07:31.560 --> 00:07:36.690
She always cries when something
scary happens in the village.

94
00:07:37.690 --> 00:07:39.270
Is it Wyper's fault...?

95
00:07:45.610 --> 00:07:46.780
It's okay, it's okay.

96
00:07:46.780 --> 00:07:48.740
I wonder.

97
00:07:49.700 --> 00:07:55.790
Whenever there's trouble,
he is always at the center of it.

98
00:07:55.790 --> 00:07:57.830
Why do you think it's him?

99
00:08:00.170 --> 00:08:02.920
There's something scary
about Wyper...

100
00:08:03.550 --> 00:08:04.590
After all...

101
00:08:04.590 --> 00:08:06.010
he's like a demon...

102
00:08:19.150 --> 00:08:20.350
The vearth!

103
00:08:23.150 --> 00:08:24.860
Wyper...!

104
00:08:24.860 --> 00:08:27.860
I told you to leave
Aisa's treasure alone!

105
00:08:27.860 --> 00:08:28.700
Stop.

106
00:08:29.490 --> 00:08:30.820
Braham!

107
00:08:31.570 --> 00:08:33.990
Don't assume we'll get
another chance!

108
00:08:34.620 --> 00:08:36.660
I won't let this opportunity
go to waste!

109
00:08:37.460 --> 00:08:40.500
Those who aren't prepared, stay here.

110
00:08:40.500 --> 00:08:42.040
I won't blame you.

111
00:08:42.040 --> 00:08:43.290
C'mon, Wyper.

112
00:08:43.290 --> 00:08:44.800
Prepared?

113
00:08:44.800 --> 00:08:46.840
We're always prepared.

114
00:08:46.840 --> 00:08:51.090
Are you prepared to abandon
those who fall along the way?

115
00:08:58.140 --> 00:09:03.110
Only follow me if you can step
over your comrades to keep moving!

116
00:09:06.440 --> 00:09:08.150
Today, Enel's head...

117
00:09:08.650 --> 00:09:10.610
will be mine!

118
00:09:14.240 --> 00:09:17.870
Until six years ago, I was god.

119
00:09:18.330 --> 00:09:20.290
Did you hit your head, old man?

120
00:09:25.290 --> 00:09:30.220
It is said that Upper Yard
appeared in Skypiea...

121
00:09:30.220 --> 00:09:35.260
some 400 years ago,
as you already know.

122
00:09:35.760 --> 00:09:40.230
The Skypiea before then
was a peaceful sky island.

123
00:09:40.640 --> 00:09:43.190
Items from the Blue Sea

124
00:09:43.190 --> 00:09:46.150
that sporadically rode
the Knock-Up Stream

125
00:09:46.150 --> 00:09:49.110
were rare and valuable
to the sky people.

126
00:09:49.990 --> 00:09:56.450
All vearth on the sky islands
came into the sky in this way.

127
00:09:57.200 --> 00:10:04.500
But receiving vearth the size of
Upper Yard was an unimaginable miracle.

128
00:10:10.380 --> 00:10:13.880
Naturally, the overjoyed
sky people worshipped it as

129
00:10:13.880 --> 00:10:15.970
holy ground bestowed
by the heavens.

130
00:10:19.850 --> 00:10:23.060
However, indigenous people
lived on this vearth,

131
00:10:23.060 --> 00:10:26.190
and a battle over its ownership began.

132
00:10:27.860 --> 00:10:30.730
Those people are the Shandians...

133
00:10:30.730 --> 00:10:32.570
You mean the guerrillas?

134
00:10:32.570 --> 00:10:33.240
Yes.

135
00:10:33.240 --> 00:10:37.740
So they originally lived
on Jaya in the world below?

136
00:10:37.740 --> 00:10:41.620
Indeed. They were sent into the sky
with the island, against their will.

137
00:10:41.620 --> 00:10:45.580
Yet, you guys kicked them
off the island?

138
00:10:45.580 --> 00:10:46.710
Yes.

139
00:10:47.330 --> 00:10:51.800
The sky people stole
their homeland out of greed...

140
00:10:52.340 --> 00:10:53.760
Even after 400 years,

141
00:10:53.760 --> 00:10:57.600
the war between the Shandians
and the sky people drags on.

142
00:10:57.600 --> 00:11:02.220
The Shandians are simply trying
to take back their homeland.

143
00:11:02.220 --> 00:11:04.600
That's... kind of heartbreaking.

144
00:11:04.600 --> 00:11:07.440
– Then aren't you the bad guys?!
– Then aren't you the bad guys?!

145
00:11:10.230 --> 00:11:13.820
Yes... That is correct.

146
00:11:16.910 --> 00:11:20.740
Oh, my medicine. Thank you.

147
00:11:22.490 --> 00:11:23.540
What about Enel?

148
00:11:25.410 --> 00:11:27.920
Who is this "God Enel"?

149
00:11:32.840 --> 00:11:35.050
When I was god,

150
00:11:35.050 --> 00:11:38.890
he suddenly appeared from
another sky island, leading an army.

151
00:11:38.890 --> 00:11:42.970
He dealt a heavy blow to
my Holy Host and the Shandians,

152
00:11:42.970 --> 00:11:45.640
and then seized
control of Upper Yard.

153
00:11:45.640 --> 00:11:47.810
This was six long years ago.

154
00:11:48.150 --> 00:11:54.190
Enel has forced most of my
Holy Host into his service.

155
00:11:54.190 --> 00:11:55.820
I do not know the details.

156
00:11:57.030 --> 00:12:02.620
But to the Shandians, god's identity
does not change the situation.

157
00:12:02.620 --> 00:12:05.330
They simply want their homeland.

158
00:12:06.290 --> 00:12:10.170
If these Shandians just want
their homeland back,

159
00:12:10.170 --> 00:12:13.750
why did they come after us
the instant we came to the sky?

160
00:12:13.750 --> 00:12:21.350
Members of the Holy Host sometimes
find a ship and manage to escape.

161
00:12:21.350 --> 00:12:26.230
Naturally, the Shandians see them
as enemies and try to eliminate them.

162
00:12:26.230 --> 00:12:28.690
Perhaps they mistook you for them.

163
00:12:29.100 --> 00:12:32.690
We were almost killed because
of a mistake? That's a bit excessive!

164
00:12:33.150 --> 00:12:35.730
One reason I became the Sky Knight

165
00:12:35.730 --> 00:12:40.660
was so that I could help those
escapees flee to other islands safely.

166
00:12:41.160 --> 00:12:45.620
As criminals, they cannot stay
in Skypiea, within Enel's reach.

167
00:12:46.370 --> 00:12:50.370
From the sound of it,
God Enel is almost like a tyrant...

168
00:12:50.370 --> 00:12:53.960
Hey, now! Watch what you say!

169
00:12:53.960 --> 00:12:57.010
The almighty God sees all!

170
00:12:57.010 --> 00:13:00.590
When did you become a Skypiean?

171
00:13:00.590 --> 00:13:03.510
D-Do you think he heard that?

172
00:13:04.310 --> 00:13:05.510
"Tyrant," you say?

173
00:13:05.510 --> 00:13:07.810
I'm afraid it is much worse than that.

174
00:13:09.600 --> 00:13:15.650
Enel establishes outsiders
like yourselves as criminals.

175
00:13:15.650 --> 00:13:21.570
Then he has the denizens of Skypiea
lead them to their reckoning.

176
00:13:22.740 --> 00:13:24.990
This causes the citizens...

177
00:13:25.490 --> 00:13:28.580
to gain a heavy sense of guilt.

178
00:13:30.910 --> 00:13:36.210
One is weakest when they are
ashamed of their own actions.

179
00:13:36.210 --> 00:13:38.510
Enel is well aware of that.

180
00:13:38.880 --> 00:13:43.090
In this process, he turns the citizens
into controllable "lost sheep."

181
00:13:44.760 --> 00:13:48.390
Enel is truly playing god.

182
00:13:48.390 --> 00:13:50.390
He is a very cunning man...

183
00:13:54.190 --> 00:13:59.150
We thought we found a paradise
when we arrived at Angel Beach...

184
00:13:59.150 --> 00:14:00.650
Boy, were we wrong...

185
00:14:01.700 --> 00:14:06.330
This is one hell of a place
the old City of Gold flew up to...

186
00:14:06.330 --> 00:14:08.240
Oh, that reminds me.

187
00:14:08.240 --> 00:14:13.920
This "gold" you've been fussing
about since last night...

188
00:14:13.920 --> 00:14:15.630
What exactly is it?

189
00:14:15.630 --> 00:14:17.090
– What?!
– What?!

190
00:14:18.500 --> 00:14:20.920
Run! It's a giant snake!

191
00:14:31.140 --> 00:14:35.650
It's enormous! Is this also a result
of the sky island's environment?

192
00:14:43.740 --> 00:14:46.660
You're like a catfish!
I'll slice you to bits!

193
00:14:55.540 --> 00:14:58.880
How the hell can something
so big move so fast?!

194
00:15:18.980 --> 00:15:20.110
Venom?!

195
00:15:20.110 --> 00:15:22.990
I think... we'd better run...

196
00:15:23.610 --> 00:15:24.780
Agreed.

197
00:15:25.110 --> 00:15:27.530
Scary!

198
00:15:29.120 --> 00:15:31.160
Don't touch the venom! It'll kill you!

199
00:15:38.670 --> 00:15:40.670
Hey! Giant venomous snake!

200
00:15:40.670 --> 00:15:43.010
Over here! Follow me!

201
00:15:43.380 --> 00:15:45.590
Your food's running away!

202
00:15:48.930 --> 00:15:51.100
Robin! Look out!

203
00:15:52.470 --> 00:15:54.060
Cinco Fleurs!

204
00:15:55.310 --> 00:15:56.230
Too bad!

205
00:15:56.230 --> 00:15:58.400
You're incredible, Robin!

206
00:16:02.900 --> 00:16:06.860
Alright! I should be
behind its tail now...

207
00:16:12.700 --> 00:16:13.540
Crap!

208
00:16:19.000 --> 00:16:20.710
This way! Over here!

209
00:16:32.600 --> 00:16:34.310
This isn't good...

210
00:16:34.680 --> 00:16:37.310
I'm back on course,
but no one's joining me...

211
00:16:37.770 --> 00:16:39.310
Did we get separated?

212
00:16:40.400 --> 00:16:43.270
Should I go ahead and wait
for them at the ruins?

213
00:16:43.270 --> 00:16:44.650
Oh, no!

214
00:16:44.650 --> 00:16:46.940
We got separated! Huh?! Huh?!

215
00:16:46.940 --> 00:16:50.240
H-Help! Where is everyone?!

216
00:16:50.740 --> 00:16:51.740
Huh?

217
00:16:51.740 --> 00:16:53.240
Where are they?

218
00:16:53.240 --> 00:16:55.450
I turn for one second,
and look what happens...

219
00:16:55.450 --> 00:16:56.660
Oh, well.

220
00:16:56.660 --> 00:16:58.960
I'm sure they'll manage somehow.

221
00:16:58.960 --> 00:17:01.580
I got most of the map
memorized, anyway.

222
00:17:01.580 --> 00:17:02.710
Just gotta go right.

223
00:17:05.210 --> 00:17:07.090
Aw, man...

224
00:17:07.090 --> 00:17:09.880
Where'd they all go?
Did they get lost?

225
00:17:09.880 --> 00:17:13.600
Whatever. Guess I'll keep going
and wait at the ruins.

226
00:17:13.600 --> 00:17:17.600
She said to go "straight south,"
and south is the warm direction!

227
00:17:17.600 --> 00:17:18.600
This way!

228
00:17:20.890 --> 00:17:25.730
When I first met you, I said
one reason I became a soldier-for-hire

229
00:17:25.730 --> 00:17:29.780
was because Blue Sea people
cannot handle sky warfare.

230
00:17:29.780 --> 00:17:32.070
Sky warfare? What's that?

231
00:17:33.490 --> 00:17:34.910
Observe.

232
00:17:34.910 --> 00:17:37.620
Why are we doing this?

233
00:17:37.620 --> 00:17:39.200
You will see.

234
00:17:39.200 --> 00:17:42.080
Try crushing that shell
with all your might.

235
00:17:42.080 --> 00:17:44.080
Don't hit it too hard, Sanji!

236
00:17:44.080 --> 00:17:47.920
If you smash a hole
in the deck, you're gonna pay!

237
00:17:47.920 --> 00:17:50.220
You may give it your all.

238
00:17:50.670 --> 00:17:54.180
Quit saying whatever you want
when it's not your ship!

239
00:17:55.180 --> 00:17:57.640
Alright, if that's what you want...

240
00:17:57.640 --> 00:18:01.690
Wait! Wait! You don't need
to swing it that hard!

241
00:18:07.270 --> 00:18:09.690
Hey, what's the deal?

242
00:18:09.690 --> 00:18:13.160
I know I told you to hold back,

243
00:18:13.160 --> 00:18:16.370
but you didn't even crack the barrel...

244
00:18:17.660 --> 00:18:20.790
No, I hit it as hard as I could.

245
00:18:20.790 --> 00:18:23.370
I was ready to put
a hole in the deck...

246
00:18:23.370 --> 00:18:24.330
Hey!

247
00:18:24.710 --> 00:18:29.460
It's like the shell
absorbed the impact...

248
00:18:31.340 --> 00:18:34.510
Now, place the dial
face down on the empty barrel

249
00:18:34.510 --> 00:18:37.470
and press the back tip of the shell.

250
00:18:38.810 --> 00:18:42.310
You know how to press it, yes?

251
00:18:45.310 --> 00:18:47.020
– Click...
– Click...

252
00:18:57.740 --> 00:19:00.450
That is an impact dial.

253
00:19:00.990 --> 00:19:05.370
It can absorb impacts and release
them with the press of a button.

254
00:19:05.920 --> 00:19:10.710
Usually, they are affixed to one's palm
using gloves or bandages.

255
00:19:11.760 --> 00:19:16.640
A direct hit is powerful enough
to kill the average person.

256
00:19:19.010 --> 00:19:21.220
Usopp, this is...

257
00:19:22.430 --> 00:19:23.180
Yeah...

258
00:19:23.180 --> 00:19:26.980
This is what that dango priest used!

259
00:19:33.610 --> 00:19:35.700
It is different from a hit!

260
00:19:35.700 --> 00:19:36.660
Impact!

261
00:19:37.110 --> 00:19:40.620
You should've said so sooner!
That freaked me out, you geezer!

262
00:19:40.990 --> 00:19:47.290
There are tales of even more powerful
dials existing on ancient sky islands.

263
00:19:47.290 --> 00:19:50.170
Take the now-extinct reject dial.

264
00:19:50.170 --> 00:19:54.970
They could release ten times
the force of an impact dial.

265
00:19:56.010 --> 00:19:58.640
However, they were
a double-edged sword.

266
00:19:58.640 --> 00:20:04.180
The excessive recoil from using them
put the user's own life at risk.

267
00:20:04.810 --> 00:20:08.940
Because of this, it seems
they were hardly ever used...

268
00:20:13.940 --> 00:20:16.570
There are shells that dangerous?!

269
00:20:16.570 --> 00:20:18.700
Those are practically weapons!

270
00:20:18.700 --> 00:20:22.410
I thought dials were more
common, everyday objects...

271
00:20:22.410 --> 00:20:24.410
Yes, they are.

272
00:20:24.410 --> 00:20:31.460
But anything that seems useful
could always be used for evil as well,

273
00:20:31.460 --> 00:20:33.880
if the user wishes it so.

274
00:20:35.170 --> 00:20:37.760
Dials are extremely useful,

275
00:20:37.760 --> 00:20:42.850
but that makes them
all the more powerful in battle.

276
00:20:43.220 --> 00:20:47.640
For example, a heat dial could be
used to both simply warm food

277
00:20:47.640 --> 00:20:54.690
and turn a spear into a controllable,
high-temperature heat javelin.

278
00:20:55.360 --> 00:21:00.740
A flame-storing flame dial,
if placed inside a bird's beak,

279
00:21:00.740 --> 00:21:03.830
creates a truly rare
fire-breathing bird...

280
00:21:03.830 --> 00:21:06.450
Y-Yeah, Chopper
mentioned stuff like that!

281
00:21:06.450 --> 00:21:08.250
And that's "sky warfare"?

282
00:21:08.250 --> 00:21:09.790
Correct.

283
00:21:10.250 --> 00:21:16.550
Blue Sea people unfamiliar with dials
cannot anticipate our techniques.

284
00:21:16.550 --> 00:21:19.420
The same is true for
the numerous artificial clouds.

285
00:21:19.420 --> 00:21:23.510
Warriors of the sky
are trained to master them;

286
00:21:23.510 --> 00:21:26.390
those with no knowledge 
of them do not stand a chance.

287
00:21:26.390 --> 00:21:30.270
Then, is there any reasoning
behind that mantra thing

288
00:21:30.270 --> 00:21:32.520
that lets them predict
our movements?

289
00:21:33.940 --> 00:21:35.400
Mantra, huh...?

290
00:21:35.400 --> 00:21:41.740
I am unable to use it myself,
so my explanation may fall short...

291
00:21:42.490 --> 00:21:45.990
but it is said that mantra
is the power to listen.

292
00:21:45.990 --> 00:21:51.250
Supposedly, just by living,
people emit voices from their bodies.

293
00:21:51.670 --> 00:21:52.620
Voices?

294
00:21:52.620 --> 00:21:53.710
Yes.

295
00:21:53.710 --> 00:21:58.210
By listening to them, one can allegedly
tell what another's next action will be.

296
00:21:58.210 --> 00:22:03.510
With further mastery, the user
can expand their hearing range.

297
00:22:04.010 --> 00:22:07.560
The priests can hear
all throughout Upper Yard,

298
00:22:07.560 --> 00:22:11.850
and Enel's powers extend
across the entire country.

299
00:22:12.600 --> 00:22:15.770
The specifics of those powers
remain a mystery.

300
00:22:16.150 --> 00:22:22.610
Because of them, the people of
this land have no time to feel at ease.

301
00:22:22.610 --> 00:22:25.620
Have they all gone down?

302
00:22:22.650 --> 00:22:28.580
God's Shrine

303
00:22:25.620 --> 00:22:26.660
Yes.

304
00:22:26.660 --> 00:22:28.580
They are eagerly waiting.

305
00:22:29.450 --> 00:22:32.120
There are the three priests' ordeals,

306
00:22:32.120 --> 00:22:35.630
on top of Abbot Yama's
fifty warrior monks...

307
00:22:36.080 --> 00:22:39.550
God, you're waging all-out war.

308
00:22:39.550 --> 00:22:43.430
Is such severity really necessary?

309
00:22:43.430 --> 00:22:47.680
We're only dealing with a few
Shandians and Blue Sea people.

310
00:22:50.350 --> 00:22:53.940
Livelier festivals are
always more enjoyable.

311
00:22:54.600 --> 00:23:00.780
Plus, you're making light of
the hidden potential of sky warfare.

312
00:23:01.110 --> 00:23:02.400
Hidden potential?

313
00:23:02.780 --> 00:23:04.530
Yes, that's right.

314
00:23:04.990 --> 00:23:07.120
They'll show you soon enough.

315
00:23:09.410 --> 00:23:10.540
Banana.

316
00:23:10.540 --> 00:23:12.330
Now, then.

317
00:23:12.910 --> 00:23:17.290
On our side, we have fifty
warrior monks and three priests.

318
00:23:17.290 --> 00:23:19.500
Including me, that makes
fifty-four people.

319
00:23:20.340 --> 00:23:23.550
Currently, there are twenty
Shandians heading for the island,

320
00:23:23.550 --> 00:23:26.300
four Blue Sea people in the forest,

321
00:23:26.300 --> 00:23:28.260
and another four trying to escape.

322
00:23:28.760 --> 00:23:31.140
Actually, make that three.

323
00:23:31.140 --> 00:23:33.270
I doubt the old man
can fight any longer.

324
00:23:33.270 --> 00:23:35.640
Eighty-one people altogether!

325
00:23:35.640 --> 00:23:38.770
This will be a battle for survival.

326
00:23:40.650 --> 00:23:45.150
Shall I guess how many will
have fallen three hours from now?

327
00:23:45.150 --> 00:23:48.160
Honestly... You're so quick
to make things into games.

328
00:23:48.160 --> 00:23:49.990
Oh, come now!

329
00:23:49.990 --> 00:23:51.740
Hey, you guess.

330
00:23:51.740 --> 00:23:54.830
What? M-Me?

331
00:23:54.830 --> 00:23:59.630
No, I have no understanding
of such things, so...

332
00:23:59.630 --> 00:24:01.880
Huh? What's with you?

333
00:24:01.880 --> 00:24:03.590
Don't be a party pooper.

334
00:24:03.590 --> 00:24:06.170
Just follow your gut.

335
00:24:06.170 --> 00:24:09.220
Fine. You, there. Take a guess!

336
00:24:09.220 --> 00:24:09.970
Huh?

337
00:24:10.930 --> 00:24:12.390
Yes...

338
00:24:12.390 --> 00:24:15.850
Well, the three priests
are powerful enough,

339
00:24:15.850 --> 00:24:19.480
but the fifty warrior monks
are also quite strong...

340
00:24:20.230 --> 00:24:23.070
which means many should
remain undefeated.

341
00:24:23.070 --> 00:24:26.400
However, the enemy is strong enough
to compete with the priests...

342
00:24:26.400 --> 00:24:30.700
So, given three hours,
I suspect thirty will fall.

343
00:24:30.700 --> 00:24:32.330
Therefore...

344
00:24:32.990 --> 00:24:34.950
about fifty will survive.

345
00:24:36.790 --> 00:24:39.830
I see! Fifty, huh?

346
00:24:39.830 --> 00:24:43.550
But don't you think that's 
a little too optimistic?

347
00:24:43.550 --> 00:24:46.090
You're underestimating
this battle, you know...

348
00:24:48.260 --> 00:24:51.300
Then, what do you predict, God?

349
00:24:52.010 --> 00:24:53.350
Alright.

350
00:24:53.350 --> 00:24:55.680
I'll give it to you straight.

351
00:24:56.270 --> 00:25:02.020
In three hours, out of
the eighty-one people in this game...

352
00:25:02.810 --> 00:25:04.190
five will remain.

353
00:25:26.590 --> 00:25:27.420
What the...?!

354
00:25:28.550 --> 00:25:29.760
My body...!

355
00:25:32.510 --> 00:25:34.180
Wh-What?!

356
00:25:34.180 --> 00:25:35.390
I can't move!

357
00:25:35.890 --> 00:25:39.060
Hello there, Shandians.

358
00:25:39.430 --> 00:25:41.640
You all look well.

359
00:25:42.730 --> 00:25:45.440
Please forgive my rude welcome.

360
00:25:47.360 --> 00:25:48.820
– Shura!
– Shura!

361
00:25:48.820 --> 00:25:50.320
Yeah, yeah.

362
00:25:50.320 --> 00:25:53.990
That's my name; don't wear it out.

363
00:25:56.580 --> 00:25:59.910
Unfortunately for all of you...

364
00:26:01.330 --> 00:26:06.710
Upper Yard's layout
has changed since last night.

365
00:26:09.010 --> 00:26:12.510
Can't move, can you? Good.

366
00:26:12.510 --> 00:26:15.260
There's a three percent survival rate...

367
00:26:16.600 --> 00:26:18.520
for this Ordeal of String!

368
00:26:23.520 --> 00:26:24.980
The Ordeal of String?!

369
00:26:25.770 --> 00:26:30.440
I would say watch out,
but it's too late for that now.

370
00:26:39.620 --> 00:26:40.870
String clouds?!

371
00:26:42.040 --> 00:26:45.130
That's right. Good job noticing them.

372
00:26:46.500 --> 00:26:51.340
All over this area are string clouds
so fine they can't be seen,

373
00:26:51.340 --> 00:26:58.050
but so strong that with enough of them,
they can stop even grown men.

374
00:26:58.600 --> 00:27:04.140
And you've been wrapping them
all over yourselves since you entered.

375
00:27:07.360 --> 00:27:10.980
Look closely.
You're covered in string!

376
00:27:10.980 --> 00:27:14.320
This is what they mean when they say
"you've dug your own grave!"

377
00:27:17.740 --> 00:27:18.700
Well...

378
00:27:19.120 --> 00:27:20.490
except for one!

379
00:27:21.910 --> 00:27:23.580
Let's go, Fuza!

380
00:27:27.250 --> 00:27:28.170
Wyper!

381
00:27:30.630 --> 00:27:33.050
Don't even think you can
match me in midair!

382
00:27:35.220 --> 00:27:37.430
Watch out! It's a heat javelin!

383
00:27:44.640 --> 00:27:46.980
Why would you throw away
your shield and gun?

384
00:27:46.980 --> 00:27:48.270
Do you have a death wish?!

385
00:27:49.770 --> 00:27:50.940
No, he wouldn't...!

386
00:27:54.530 --> 00:27:58.910
If you want my shoulder,
you can have it.

387
00:28:03.790 --> 00:28:06.920
An impact dial, huh?!
Such things can't defeat me!

388
00:28:07.330 --> 00:28:10.920
No, it's ten times stronger.

389
00:28:12.050 --> 00:28:13.250
Reject!

390
00:28:41.120 --> 00:28:46.410
The Upper Yard survival game
has had its first casualty.

391
00:28:46.410 --> 00:28:48.290
Now eighty remain.

392
00:28:49.000 --> 00:28:52.130
The first battle ends in a great upset...

393
00:28:52.130 --> 00:28:53.710
Shura has been defeated.

394
00:28:53.710 --> 00:28:56.010
M-My word! Lord Shura defeated?!

395
00:28:56.010 --> 00:29:01.050
He underestimated
sky warfare, too. The fool!

396
00:29:04.100 --> 00:29:06.720
But is this not cause for distress?!

397
00:29:06.720 --> 00:29:11.520
Two priests, undefeated for six years,
suddenly fall in under two days!

398
00:29:11.520 --> 00:29:12.900
It's fine.

399
00:29:12.900 --> 00:29:15.480
They were defeated and that's that.

400
00:29:16.730 --> 00:29:20.240
They must have lacked
God's divine protection...

401
00:29:25.700 --> 00:29:27.330
Alright, men!

402
00:29:27.330 --> 00:29:31.250
We're up against twenty Shandians
and seven Blue Sea people.

403
00:29:31.250 --> 00:29:32.750
This will be easy.

404
00:29:32.750 --> 00:29:35.800
There is no need to even trouble
the priests with them.

405
00:29:36.170 --> 00:29:39.090
Go and wreak havoc
to your hearts' content!

406
00:29:39.090 --> 00:29:42.640
50 Warrior Monks
Skypiea

407
00:29:45.050 --> 00:29:50.310
Only follow me if you can step
over your comrades to keep moving!

408
00:29:51.020 --> 00:29:54.980
Today... Enel's head will be mine!

409
00:29:58.780 --> 00:30:00.280
Once we defeat Enel,

410
00:30:00.280 --> 00:30:04.740
we won't be needing to revere
a single bag of vearth any longer.

411
00:30:12.210 --> 00:30:15.340
...a single bag of vearth...

412
00:30:25.600 --> 00:30:27.850
Wyper! Are you trying
to kill yourself?!

413
00:30:27.850 --> 00:30:33.390
If you use that reject dial even once
more, your body will be blown apart!

414
00:30:40.110 --> 00:30:41.860
I'm prepared to sacrifice my body.

415
00:30:41.860 --> 00:30:44.240
Are you questioning my resolve?!

416
00:30:44.740 --> 00:30:48.740
These guys can't be beaten
without such sacrifices!

417
00:31:06.300 --> 00:31:07.550
That bastard!

418
00:31:07.550 --> 00:31:10.140
What are you standin' around for?

419
00:31:10.140 --> 00:31:11.430
Braham!

420
00:31:12.060 --> 00:31:14.390
We're behind enemy lines now.

421
00:31:14.390 --> 00:31:15.560
Let's split up.

422
00:31:15.560 --> 00:31:17.770
There are still two priests left.

423
00:31:18.730 --> 00:31:21.530
Seems they've changed
the locations of the ordeals.

424
00:31:22.240 --> 00:31:25.610
We don't wanna all get caught
in the same one again, do we?

425
00:31:25.610 --> 00:31:28.200
There's no reason to be that stupid...

426
00:31:28.200 --> 00:31:29.580
I'm going on ahead!

427
00:31:32.790 --> 00:31:35.250
Fine! Do what you want!

428
00:31:35.250 --> 00:31:37.920
I wish you all good luck!

429
00:31:40.340 --> 00:31:42.420
Alright, guys! Be careful out there!

430
00:31:43.010 --> 00:31:44.880
Let's meet at God's Shrine!

431
00:31:58.650 --> 00:32:00.650
Who are you?! What did you do?!

432
00:32:01.820 --> 00:32:02.980
Heso!

433
00:32:02.980 --> 00:32:04.150
A warrior monk?!

434
00:32:04.150 --> 00:32:05.110
Indeed!

435
00:32:05.110 --> 00:32:11.120
By God Enel's orders, we've been sent
to clean out all of Upper Yaard!

436
00:32:11.120 --> 00:32:16.080
Accept the faact that there is no escape
from us fifty elite warrior monks!

437
00:32:17.580 --> 00:32:22.460
Taste the wraath of the axe dial,
which cannot be found in Skypiea!

438
00:32:23.670 --> 00:32:25.050
Just get out of my way!

439
00:32:27.430 --> 00:32:29.800
Even deeper! Even sharper!

440
00:32:31.350 --> 00:32:32.720
Axe Dial!

441
00:32:34.060 --> 00:32:35.270
Shields have no effect!

442
00:32:57.660 --> 00:33:00.630
♪ Oh, the islands in the south... ♪

443
00:33:00.630 --> 00:33:02.630
♪ are all warm... ♪

444
00:33:02.630 --> 00:33:05.630
♪ Pineapple-apple, head all molten, ♪

445
00:33:05.630 --> 00:33:08.760
♪ full of dummies... ♪

446
00:33:10.680 --> 00:33:11.970
A goat?

447
00:33:11.970 --> 00:33:13.550
Was that a goat?

448
00:33:13.550 --> 00:33:14.640
Where is it?

449
00:33:17.850 --> 00:33:19.350
A goat in a forest?

450
00:33:30.240 --> 00:33:31.740
Aw, man!

451
00:33:31.740 --> 00:33:33.620
Jerk got me all excited!

452
00:33:33.620 --> 00:33:36.080
I wanted to see a goat!

453
00:33:39.870 --> 00:33:40.620
Second verse!

454
00:33:40.620 --> 00:33:43.630
♪ Oh, the islands in the north... ♪

455
00:33:43.630 --> 00:33:45.210
♪ are all cold... ♪

456
00:33:45.210 --> 00:33:48.760
♪ Super chilly, brains all shivery, ♪

457
00:33:48.760 --> 00:33:52.010
♪ full of dummies... ♪

458
00:33:54.930 --> 00:33:57.010
Oh, it's you!

459
00:33:58.020 --> 00:33:59.310
What...

460
00:33:59.890 --> 00:34:01.730
are you doing here?

461
00:34:02.270 --> 00:34:05.190
I warned you to leave this island!

462
00:34:05.190 --> 00:34:06.270
Shut up!

463
00:34:06.270 --> 00:34:07.820
I can do whatever I want.

464
00:34:07.820 --> 00:34:09.690
No, you can't.

465
00:34:09.690 --> 00:34:13.030
This island belongs to us Shandians!

466
00:34:13.030 --> 00:34:14.070
Huh?

467
00:34:14.070 --> 00:34:15.280
It does?

468
00:34:15.280 --> 00:34:17.330
I thought it belonged to that god...

469
00:34:17.330 --> 00:34:18.620
Really?

470
00:34:18.620 --> 00:34:20.660
Well, thanks for having me.

471
00:34:22.920 --> 00:34:23.960
Third verse!

472
00:34:23.960 --> 00:34:25.790
♪ Oh, the islands in the east– ♪

473
00:34:24.500 --> 00:34:25.790
Wait!

474
00:34:25.790 --> 00:34:26.750
What do you want?!

475
00:34:27.710 --> 00:34:28.880
No.

476
00:34:28.880 --> 00:34:30.920
I have nothing to say to you.

477
00:34:32.930 --> 00:34:36.430
Nor do I want to hear
any of your garbage.

478
00:34:38.310 --> 00:34:40.020
I just want to eliminate you!

479
00:34:41.100 --> 00:34:42.310
Oh.

480
00:34:47.650 --> 00:34:49.900
That makes things
simple enough then!
